#
# Config for dissociation of H2 (and other species) by LW photons: works with the data containers in KROME
# Shyam Harimohan Menon, 2023
#

D Manual: H2 dissociation is done in-house in VETTAM; PrimKrome: Primordial chemistry with KROME; MetalKrome: Metal chemistry with KROME
DEFAULT Manual
EXCLUSIVE Manual PrimKrome MetalKrome

REQUIRES physics/RadTrans/RadTransMain/VETTAM
REQUIRES physics/RadTrans/RadTransMain/VETTAM/RayTrace

D flag to use ionising radiation module
PARAMETER useH2Dissociate   BOOLEAN  TRUE

D H2 dissociation type
PARAMETER lwdiss_type  STRING  "raytrace"

D Doppler b parameter used in fshield equation in units of km/s (see Draine and Bertoldi 1996); default value of 1
PARAMETER   bfive   REAL    1.0 

D The parameter fpump that quantifies the probability of UV pumping vs dissociation; Eq 45 of Baczynski et al 2015
PARAMETER   fpump   REAL    6.94

D The thermal energy deposited per photodissociation event; using 0.4 eV by default (Black & Dalgarno 1977)
PARAMETER   energyPerDissociation  REAL  6.408705848000027e-13

D The average energy of a LW photon -- this would depend on the spectrum, but we use 12.2 eV by default -- typical of a stellar population (Kim+ 23)
PARAMETER   avgEnergyLW     REAL     1.954655283640008e-11

D Flag to switch on/off H2 shielding due to H
PARAMETER   useHIshield     BOOLEAN     TRUE

D Variable Storing the Shielding Factor of mol H2 for the cell
VARIABLE FSHM

D Variable Storing the Shielding Factor of atomic H2 for the cell
VARIABLE FSHA

D Variable storing the self-shielded LW dissociation flux
VARIABLE LWFL


